ON WEDNESDAY EVENING SLACK AREAS OF LOW PRESSURE
GENERALLY DOMINATE THE SHIPPING AREAS. A LOW 1000 SERN
NORWEGIAN SEA IS SLOW MOV WHILST A FLN LOW IS CENTRED
OVER ROCKALL AND MALIN WITH FURTHER WEAK LOWS CENTRED E
FITZROY AND DUE S OF ICELAND. HIGH PRESSURE EXISTS W OF
FITZROY AND OVER THE MEDITERRANEAN. THE RIDGE OF HIGH
PRESSURE W OF FITZROY EDGES FURTHER E OVERNIGHT AND INTO
THURSDAY BLDN OVER THE UK WITH THE VARIOUS LOW PRESSURE
CENTRES CONTINUING TO FILL. MEANWHILE A NEW AREA OF LOW
PRESSURE 1002 DEVELOPS S SPAIN. BY FRIDAY MORE
SUBSTANTIAL LOW PRESSURE OVER THE N ATLANTIC WILL START
TO PUSH INTO NWERN AREAS AND DISPLACE THE HIGH PRESSURE
INTO THE CONTINENT. MAINLY LIGHT WINDS INITIALLY BUT S
OR SE GALES LIKELY TO SPREAD ACROSS WERN PORTPATRICK
THURSDAY NIGHT INTO FRIDAY MORNING SPREADING E TO ALL
